With toothpick, spread chocolate to make cat shape.

title: quick beer rolls
directions: Mix Bisquick and sugar well.
Add beer.
Beat and pour into well-greased muffin tin.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Mix
together the soups, steak and mushrooms.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake, covered, for 2 1/2 hours at 325° or longer.
Add
ounces
sour
cream to meat mixture. Serve over cooked noodles.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In a 13 x 9-inch cake pan, melt margarine in oven. Sprinkle crumbs over margarine. Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Press down.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool.
Chill, if desired. Cut into bars. Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: strawberry banana salad
directions: In a bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in strawberries, pineapple, bananas, and nuts.
Pour half of mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2 in. dish.
Refrigerate for 1 hour or until set. Set the remaining gelatin mixture aside.
Combine the sour cream, sugar, and vanilla; mix well.
Spread over the chilled gelatin. Spoon remaining gelatin mixture over top.
Chill overnight.
Yield: 12 - 15 servings.

title: cutout chocolate cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, egg and vanilla until light and fluffy. Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Chill dough about 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 325°.
On lightly floured surface or between 2 pieces of waxed paper roll small portion at a time to 1/4 inch thickness. Cut into shapes.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 5 to 7 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Remove and frost.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: carrot bread
directions: Beat eggs; stir in remaining ingredients.
Place into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: delicious fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Save juice from the pineapple and fruit cocktail.
Mix juice with instant pudding.
Stir until thick. Pour over fruit.
Add sliced bananas and cherries.
Chill.

title: sweet and sour sausage
directions: Slice sausage in quarter slices.
Brown on both sides.
Drain off fat.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: hot dip snacks
directions: Cook sausage, stirring as to blend.
Saute jalapenos in this until changes color.
Add cheese, stirring constantly to melt cheese and mix well.
Pour in shallow dish and cool.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In saucepan, combine sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in undrained pineapple, sour cream and lemon juice until thoroughly blended.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles; cook and stir 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir a moderate amount of hot mixture into egg yolks; return to hot mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more. Spoon hot mixture into cooled pastry shell.
Spread meringue atop pie, sealing meringue to edge of pastry.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until golden.
Cool before cutting.

title: pork and sausage jambalaya
directions: Put 1 cup water in pot.
Add cubed pork and start browning. When pork turns light brown, add sausage and brown until dark brown.
Remove excess grease from pot.
Brown onions.
Add green onions and bell pepper.
Cook down.
Add 4 cups water.
Add seasoning and bring to a boil.
Add rice and stir until water becomes thick.
Cover and put fire as low as possible.
Wait 10 minutes and turn rice over (do not stir) from the bottom of the pot.
Re-cover.
Wait 10 minutes and turn over again.
Turn fire off.
Let sit 5 minutes and serve.

title: heavenly fruit dip
directions: Cook all the ingredients except Cool Whip over medium heat until thick.
Cool in refrigerator for 2 hours. Fold in 1 cup Cool Whip.
Store in refrigerator.

title: pork chops and browned rice
directions: Brown chops and set aside.
Pour rice into pan where chops were browned.
Stir constantly until golden brown, about 10 minutes.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add bouillon water; simmer over low heat until liquid is gone, 20 to 25 minutes.
Lay chops on top of rice for the last 10 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except Tater Tots in large casserole dish. Cover with 1 layer of Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange cake
directions: Mix all together and beat until orange slices are broken up and fluffy.
Pour into three 8-inch cake pans.
Grease and flour pans. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together the first 2 ingredients and then spread on large platter.
Layer on top of that mixture the remaining listed ingredients in the order given.
Refrigerate.
Serve with taco chips.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo in skillet.
Stir in flour and dry mustard. Season with salt and pepper.
Add milk.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Alternate layers of potatoes, celery, ham, green pepper and cheese sauce in 9 x 13-inch pan until all ingredients are used, ending with cheese sauce.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and refrigerate until used.

title: sweet 'n sour cabbage and kielbasa saute
directions: In 10-inch skillet, heat oil.
Add kielbasa and onions and saute until browned.
Add cabbage and stir thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients and cook, stirring occasionally, until cabbage is tender and liquid has evaporated.
Makes 2 servings.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Make cake according to package directions.
Pour into rectangular pan and bake.
Cool and cut in half.
Make pudding, using 2 1/2 cups milk per package.

title: pinto bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Add pinto beans, tomato sauce, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Spray baking dish with Pam.
Pour meat mixture into baking dish.

title: won ton mushroom ravioli with mushroom sauce
directions: Food process mushrooms coarse rather than fine.
Pit olives and process finer than mushrooms.
Heat butter and oil in skillet.
Add onion, oregano, parsley and mushrooms.
Salt lightly and cook over brisk heat, stirring constantly 5 to 6 minutes.
Mushrooms should start to color and onion softens.
Add garlic during the last few minutes of cooking so it doesn't burn pepper.
Set aside.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in a small amount of salted water until tender; drain.
Add bread or cracker crumbs (reserving 1 tablespoon for top), cheese, egg, salt, pepper and 2 tablespoons margarine.
Spoon into greased casserole.
Top with remaining crumbs; dot with 2 tablespoons margarine.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until brown.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: turkey chili
directions: Saute onions and garlic over low heat.
Add turkey hamburger to saucepot.
Cover.
Stir frequently until meat is lightly cooked and separated.
Add chili powder, tomatoes and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Uncover; add drained kidney beans to sauce.
Cook slowly about 30 minutes.
Add tomato puree with a little water if mixture is too thick.
Tastes better when cooked in advance (24 hours).

title: dirt
directions: Cream margarine and cream cheese; add powdered sugar, mixing well.
Set aside.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Use 1 1/2 cups liquid; if not enough, add water.
Mix with pudding mix and cook until thick. Then cool.
Add fruit and mix.
Add bananas and cherries last and mix gently.

title: butterhorn rolls
directions: Soften yeast in 3 tablespoons warm water.
Combine sugar, shortening, 1 cup warm water, salt and eggs in large bowl.
Mix well.
Add yeast and flour; beat until smooth.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: mission fact treats
directions: Mix peanut butter and marshmallow cream in a bowl until smooth.
Roll dough into small balls.
Roll balls in graham cracker crumbs.
Place balls on waxed paper.
Stick toothpicks into the balls.

title: spicy shrimp-noodle soup
directions: Combine lemon juice, chili powder, cumin and pepper.
Add shrimp.
Toss to coat.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until fork-tender.
Drain and cool slightly. In a large bowl, combine potatoes and all other ingredients; toss gently to mix well.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Cover.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours for best taste.

title: instant chocolate pie
directions: Prepare pudding mix according to directions, using only 1 cup milk.
Blend in 1 1/2 cups whipped topping and 1/4 cup pecans. Spoon into pie shell.
Decorate with remaining 1/2 cup whipped topping and additional nuts.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: mama's potato salad
directions: In a large kettle, cook potatoes in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain and cool.
Peel potatoes; cut into chunks. Separate egg yolks from whites.
Set yolks aside.
Chop whites and add to potatoes with onion.

title: soupe aux legumes
directions: Heat oil in deep heavy pan and add the onions, carrots, celery, turnips and potatoes.
Cook for a few minutes; then add the green beans.
Cook the vegetables for another 5 to 10 minutes. Add the stock and vermicelli and season with salt to taste. Reduce heat and simmer until vegetables are tender but still crisp.
Add the peas to the soup with the spinach, tomatoes and zucchini.
Continue cooking for another 20 to 30 minutes.
This keeps well for several days in the fridge.
Serve with a dollop of pesto sauce and hot French bread.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together in mixing bowl.
Drop dough by spoonfuls on lightly greased cookie sheet. Press with a fork.
Bake in oven for 5 to 8 minutes or until light brown.

title: grandma's macaroni pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Divide macaroni and cheese into two parts.
Layer 1/2 macaroni, then 1/2 grated cheese in 2-quart buttered baking dish.
Repeat with second layer, finishing with cheese.
Dissolve the mustard and salt in 1/4 cup milk.
Beat eggs; stir in mustard mixture and rest of milk.
Pour over macaroni and cheese.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes or until knife stuck
comes out clean.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix well together.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: golden brownies
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine and pour into an oblong pan.
Mix all chips and crushed wafers.
Pour condensed milk over mixture.
Mix. Pour into pan.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes, until golden.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Beat cream cheese, gradually adding milk.
Beat until smooth. Add lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, garlic, salt and pepper. Add shrimp and stir in cream cheese mixture.
Chill.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups dip.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and cut up eggplant.
Then boil until they are done enough to mash up.
Remove from the boiling water and mash the eggplant.
Then add cream of chicken soup, onion (chopped), eggs, salt, pepper, cornbread (crumbled), light bread and sage to your taste.
Mix well.

title: katy's delight
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in cottage cheese.
Mix well.
Drain and add oranges and pineapple.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: famous pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°. Continue baking 45 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool completely and garnish, if desired, with whipped cream.

title: cauliflower slaw
directions: Slice raw cauliflower thin.
Combine with other ingredients. Serve in salad bowl.
Salt to taste.
Chill overnight.

title: risotto
directions: Brown chopped onion and rice in hot oiled pan.
Add water and bouillon.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes.
Turn off.
Add Cheddar cheese.
Serve with meat, vegetables and rolls.

title: stove top baked beans
directions: In skillet, cook bacon or ground beef.
Use meat drippings to cook onion and bell pepper.
Drain.
Add all ingredients.
Bring to boil, then simmer for 20 minutes.

title: rolls
directions: Put shortening and milk in saucepan; let heat until shortening melts.
(We use oleomargarine.)
Remove from heat and let cool. In a large mixing bowl, dissolve the yeast in water.
Add sugar and salt.
Add the cooked milk mixture and the beaten eggs (whole), then sifted flour.
Mix well.
Cover the bowl with cloth or waxed paper.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Turn on lightly floured board and knead lightly.
Roll out 1/4-inch thin.
Spread with melted butter and fold over to make two layers.
Cut in shapes.
Place about 1/2-inch apart to rise in greased pans.
Let rise again until double in bulk (about 2 hours).
Bake in medium oven at 350° for about 10 to 15 minutes.
This will make 40 extra large rolls.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling water until tender.
Drain.
Arrange broccoli in greased 11 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch dish.
Place chicken on top.
Combine soup, curry powder, mayonnaise and lemon juice. Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine bread crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle over mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: date pudding
directions: Mix
all
dry
ingredients
together.
Add
milk and egg whites, beaten stiff.
Set in pan of water and bake in moderate oven for 50 minutes.
Take out of pan of water last 5 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place cooked broccoli in greased casserole.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sharp, grated cheese over top.
Top with 3/4 cup fresh bread crumbs. Melt 1 tablespoon margarine and dribble over top.
Bake until bubbly, approximately 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: braunschweiger ball
directions: Bring cream cheese and braunschweiger to room temperature. Combine half of the cream cheese with remaining ingredients except nuts. Mix well.
Spread in mold and chill for several hours. Unmold.
Frost with remaining cream cheese.
Garnish with chopped nuts.
Serve with crackers or a party loaf bread.

title: pennsylvania dutch sugar cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Mix in beaten eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternately with sour milk.
Add almonds and vanilla flavorings.
Pour into 3 greased 8-inch pie pans.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon sugar on top of each. Bake at 350° about 25 minutes.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Place cream cheese in a bowl and stir until very smooth.
Add all remaining ingredients and stir until thoroughly blended. Transfer to serving bowl and garnish with sliced olives, if desired.
Serve with assorted crackers.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: peanut butter rocky road fudge
directions: Place chocolate chips, peanut butter chips and the peanut butter in 2-quart dish in microwave, uncovered, on Medium until melted, 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir until smooth.
Mix in marshmallows and peanuts until evenly coated; spread in buttered square 8 x 8 pan.
Refrigerate until firm, at least 1 hour; cut into bars.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with seasoned salt; place in crock-pot on high.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Cook for 3 to 4 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve over cooked rice. Enjoy!

title: oyster rockefeller soup
directions: Cook spinach in the bouillon.
Puree in food processor with oysters.
Add enough milk to make 1 quart of soup.
Serves 4.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix together and shape into loaf.
Place in casserole and pour over it a syrup made of 1 cup brown sugar, 1/2 cup vinegar and 2/3 cup water.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Baste with syrup 3 or 4 times.

title: quick shaker cake
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and shake (mix or blend), then add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased 8-inch square pan and bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Top with fresh strawberries and whipped topping when completely cooled.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs in bowl until light and fluffy. Add mixture of cocoa and food coloring; mix well.
Add salt, buttermilk, flour and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in mixture of vinegar and baking soda.
Spoon into 2 greased and floured 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Split layers horizontally; spread with Fluffy White Frosting between layers and over top of cake.

title: bagel chips
directions: Heat oven to 325°. Mix oil, margarine and garlic; brush onto bagel slices.
Bake slices on cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes or until bagels are crisp.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: barbecue roast
directions: Put inside cooking bag (make few slits in top of bag).
Put cooking bag inside crock-pot.
Cook approximately 10 hours on low. Take the roast out of the crock-pot and cooking bag and tear up with a fork, then put the roast back in crock-pot.
Cover with barbecue sauce and heat until hot through.

title: wild berry cobbler
directions: Place butter in a 2 qt. rectangular baking dish.
Heat in oven for 5 minutes until butter is melted.
Remove dish from oven. Stir together, flour, sugar, powder and salt.
Add milk and stir until just combined.
Pour this over melted butter; do not stir. Spoon fruit over batter.

title: hush puppies
directions: In bowl, combine cornmeal, flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Add onion, buttermilk and then egg; blend.
Drop from tablespoon, a few at a time, into deep shortening heated to 375°. Fry
until golden.
Drain on paper toweling.

title: wackey cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Add the liquids.
Mix and bake in moderate oven 350° for 30-35 minutes.

title: chicken and creamed noodles
directions: Bake chicken at 350° for 30 minutes; drain juice off the chicken.
Add the noodles.
Mix water and soup; pour over the chicken.
Sprinkle spices from the noodle packs over the chicken. Bake for 30 minutes in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
If the noodles are not tender, cook a little longer.

title: celery seed salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Keep refrigerated.
This recipe makes enough to keep extra on hand.

title: old fashion pumpkin pie filling or sweet potato
directions: Beat all ingredients well.
Pour into 9-inch deep dish pie shell.
Bake at 425°
for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350° and bake
45 minutes more until knife inserted comes out clean.
Cool.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Mix sugar and molasses.
Add melted shortening and eggs; mix well.
Add vanilla.
Dissolve the soda in hot water.
Sift flour, cream of tartar, spices and salt together, then mix all together. Let mixed dough stand in a cool place for 1 hour.
Roll out to about 1/8-inch thick.
Bake at 350° on a well-greased cookie tin for 10 minutes, or until well done.

title: turkey
directions: Have turkey at room temperature.
Rub inside and out with salt.
Preheat oven to 475°.

title: pinto beans
directions: Soak beans overnight in large pot.
Drain and rinse thoroughly.
Put back in large pot; cover with cold water.
Add salt and bacon or bacon grease.
Cook slowly for several hours until tender and nice broth has formed.
Enjoy with corn bread and onions.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Bring water and tea to gentle boil and let steep; add sugar. Remove tea bags, pour into 1 gallon container.
Add Ocean Spray cranberry juice concentrate.
Fill remainder of container with cool water.
Serve hot or cold with lemon wedge or cinnamon stick.

title: favorite pancakes
directions: Beat egg well.
Add milk and soda.
Beat in the rest of ingredients until smooth.
Cook on heavy griddle.
Makes about 16 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: egg foo yong
directions: Combine eggs, bean sprouts, meat or seafood, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix together lightly. Melt 1 teaspoon butter in 6-inch skillet.
Pack 1/2 cup of mixture into skillet.
Cook until set and brown on edges.
Turn and brown on other side.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients one minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Press into greased pan.
Cut into squares.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Cook beans according to package directions.
Add meat and all ingredients and simmer together for about 4 hours.
Smash several beans on the side of the pan.

title: sour cream-lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, lemon rind, juice, egg yolks and milk in a heavy saucepan; cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Stir in butter and cool mixture to room temperature.
Stir in sour cream and pour into pie shell.
Cover with whipped cream and garnish with lemon twists.
Store in refrigerator.

title: hermits(portuguese)
directions: Combine ingredients. Drop in spoonfuls on buttered pan or cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together except oil.
Heat oil in 10-inch iron skillet.
Pour hot oil into cornbread mix.
Blend.
Pour mixture into hot skillet.
Bake at 425° until done, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: diabetic low calorie punch
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add 7-Up and ice ring just prior to serving.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Combine ingredients as listed.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked fish
directions: Salt and pepper fish.
Arrange pepper slices and onion slices over fish.
Mix chicken broth, lemon juice and basil.
Pour mixture over fish.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt into mixing bowl.
Add egg and creamed corn, mix well.
Heat corn oil in skillet.
Drop corn mixture by tablespoons into hot corn oil and fry until golden brown on both sides.
Makes 18.

title: blizzard of 1993 soup
directions: Soak beans for several hours.
Wash and put in a large pot and cover with 3-quarts water.
Add onions and garlic, both slightly browned in butter.
Salt to taste.
Add ham hock, parsley, bay leaves, juice of 1/2 lemon and several drops of Tabasco sauce. Cover and cook slowly for 3 to 4 hours.
Add smoked sausage and pepper to taste and cook about 45 minutes longer.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake in 2 layers.
Put one layer, broken in pieces, in bottom of bowl and add 1/2 pie filling, 1/2 crushed pineapple and 1/2 nuts.
Repeat with second layer of cake.
Add cherries last. Refrigerate.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet and cut up onion. Cook until the onion is tender. Add soups; stir until smooth. Add 1/2 cup of milk. Debone chicken; layer chicken, rice and soup mixture. Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: clam chowder
directions: Fry first four ingredients in butter or margarine. Add remaining ingredients; simmer until the potatoes are soft, but firm. Add light cream and a pinch of sugar to the pot. Serve with a baguette and a nice white wine. BON APPETITE!

title: oven browned potatoes
directions: In a large plastic bag or bowl with secure lid, combine all ingredients.
Shake to be sure all potato pieces are coated with oil and onion soup mix.
Pour coated potatoes into medium size casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir once during cook time.

title: quick chicken pie
directions: Cook and take chicken off bone.
Reserve 2 cups broth.
Cut chicken into pieces and place in bottom of baking dish.
Melt margarine and pour over chicken.
Mix together dry ingredients and mix well with milk.
Pour over chicken.
Heat soup and broth to the boiling point and pour over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes its own crust.

title: zucchini sweet pickles
directions: In a large canner container, add zucchini, water and lime. Soak, weighted down, overnight. Drain and wash well.
Cover with clean water. Let stand for 2
hours and drain.

title: new england dinner
directions: In a large pan, put water.
Cut potatoes, carrots and onion up. Put into pan.
Cut sausage up.
Lay on top of vegetables.
Quarter cabbage and put on top.
Bring water to boil.
Cook until done. Place on large platter.
Serve.
Put salt and pepper to season. Add butter to season also.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Mix well.
Make into walnut size balls, mash down and put on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown steak in hot fat. Add all other ingredients. Simmer in a pan for 2 hours or in pressure cooker for 15 minutes at 10 pounds pressure. Serve over rice.

title: rice chicken dinner
directions: Put rice in bottom of greased roasting pan.
Place serving pieces of chicken on top.
Pour the can of soup over.
Pour water over all.
Sprinkle dry soup mix on top.
Cover and bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: crispy rice-peanut butter sandwich
directions: Make spread out of first 3 ingredients.
Place mixture between bread slices.
Serves 4.

title: easy fettuccine
directions: Cook pasta as directed on package. In a large pan, melt butter slowly. Add drained noodles. Pour in Sweet Sue chicken broth, half and half, garlic powder, grated cheese, salt and pepper to taste. Gently stir until heated and the cheese is melted. Yield: 6 servings.

title: braided sausage bread
directions: Place wide ends of crescent rolls together. Roll into rectangle shape on cookie sheet that's been sprayed with Pam. In large skillet, brown sausage; drain. Add chopped green onions, chopped celery, chopped onions, chopped bell pepper and minced garlic clove. Cook until vegetables are tender. Add cream cheese. Keep stirring until melted. Let cool. Place down middle of rectangle. Cut strips down each long side crisscross over top of sausage mix. Bake in oven preheated to 375° for 20 to 25 minutes, until golden brown.

title: twinki cake
directions: Mix and bake cake mix according to box instructions.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and split cake (best use a thread).
Take top layer off and ice first layer with filling.
Replace second layer on top and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chocolate chip muffins
directions: Beat egg; stir in milk and oil.
Stir in remaining ingredients except chocolate chips just until flour is moistened (don't overmix).
Fold in chocolate chips.
Put batter into a dozen paper muffin cups and bake about 20 minutes.

title: shrimp canapes
directions: Mix shrimp, onion, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Spread on Ritz crackers or Club crackers.
Place slice of cheese on shrimp and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until cheese starts to melt.
Serve hot.

title: appetizer cheese sandwiches
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well and chill before spreading.
Trim whole wheat bread slices and spread with mixture.
Cut into 3 fingers. Refrigerate until serving.

title: no cook divinity
directions: Combine frosting mix (dry), corn syrup, vanilla and boiling water in a small mixer bowl.
Beat on highest speed until stiff peaks form, about 5 minutes.
Transfer to a large mixer bowl.
On low speed or by hand gradually blend in sugar.
Stir in nuts. Drop mixture by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
When outside of candy feels firm, turn over and allow to dry at least 12 hours.
Store candy in airtight container.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen pieces.
tags: Betty Crocker fluffy white frosting mix

title: gingerbread
directions: Sift together the flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, ginger, allspice and cloves.
Melt shortening in hot water.
Add molasses and stir.
Pour liquid mixture into flour mixture and beat well. Pour into an 8-inch square greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until top of gingerbread is light brown and springs back to the touch.
Serve warm and top with whipped cream, if desired.

title: australian pavlova
directions: Beat egg whites with electric mixer until stiff and dry. Gradually add sugar until all the sugar is dissolved.
Mix baking powder and cornstarch together.
Sprinkle over meringue while mixing.
Add vanilla and vinegar.
Beat for another minute. Preheat oven to 300°.
Line a cookie sheet with aluminum foil. Grease foil and sprinkle with cornstarch.
Mark out an 8-inch circle on the foil and spoon meringue into circle, heaping it up in the center as much as possible.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and cream cheese together until light and fluffy, then add sugar.
Cream until fluffy.
Add sugar and cream until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, then add flavoring.
Add flour.
Pour into tube, Bundt pan or loaf pans.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until tested done.

title: sock-it-to-me cake
directions: Mix brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour 1/2 batter in greased Teflon Bundt pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar and cinnamon over.
Add rest of cake batter on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Glaze.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt, sugar and cereal.
Add milk, shortening and eggs.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes or microwave on Medium 4 1/2 minutes.
Unbaked batter keeps in Tupperware in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks.

title: mock boursin cheese
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Chill a few hours.
Serve with crackers or fill small puffs.
Will keep a week refrigerated.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla. Add flour, spices and soda.
Stir in oats.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 9 minutes for soft cookies.

title: apple pie in a bucket
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan. Cook for 15 to 20 minutes until liquid is clear and slightly thickens.
Apples do not need to be done. Cool. Pour into an ice cream bucket. Freeze. Two batches fill one bucket. Thaw for 1 hour to get enough to fill a pie when needed.

title: beef shortribs supreme
directions: Brown shortribs on all sides in a large skillet without shortening. Cover and cook over low heat 1 hour. Drain off drippings. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over ribs. Cover and cook over low heat 1 1/2 hours. Serve over mashed potatoes.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and pour over crackers.
Mix until crackers have "dull" finish.
Store in airtight container.

title: hot punch
directions: Simmer ingredients 10 minutes before serving.
Add small amount of butter in each cup for serving, if desired.

title: quick green beans
directions: Stir flour, salt and pepper into melted butter in saucepan. Stir in milk.
Cook until thickened.
Pour over green beans. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Brown under broiler.

title: magic pumpkin pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, blend together all ingredients.
Turn mixture into pie shell.
Bake in 375° oven until sharp bladed knife inserted near center comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool. Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
May press 1/4 cup chopped pecans into shell before pouring in filling.

title: one dish chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 3 quart casserole dish, place uncooked rice.
Sprinkle onion soup mix on top of rice, spoon cream of celery on next.
Pour boiling water over the whole thing. Place chicken on top.
Bake uncovered for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pickled cauliflower and carrots
directions: Cut cauliflower and put in bowl with 2 tablespoons salt.
Do the same with carrots; let stand 2 hours.
Rinse and drain. Combine vinegar, sugar, onion flakes, mustard seed, turmeric and peppercorns.
Bring to a boil; add carrots and return to boil. Simmer 5 minutes.
Add cauliflower; return to boil and simmer 8 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: amish yeast bread
directions: Scald milk; remove from heat.
Add 1/4 cup sugar, salt, butter and mashed potatoes.
Cool.
Dissolve yeast in water, then mix with milk.
Add raisins and flour.
Stir.
Let rise in warm place 1 1/2 hours.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute hamburger, pepper and onions until meat is done.
Add salt, pepper and soups.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Before serving, add 1 container of sour cream.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: microwave baked lima beans
directions: You will need a 3-quart microwave-safe casserole.

title: turtle cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Pour 1/2 batter into a Pam-sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for only 15 minutes.
In top of double boiler over hot water, melt together caramels, milk and butter.
Pour this over baked portion of the cake.
Sprinkle the pecans and chocolate chips over the caramel mixture.
Spread the remaining batter over this mixture.
Bake an additional 20 to 30 minutes.

title: blondies
directions: Preset oven to 325°. Line 13 x 9-inch metal pan or butter it. Cook in center. Melt butter and white chocolate over low heat (or microwave). Stir until smooth. Cool for 10 minutes. Stir in sugar and eggs (one at a time), using a wooden spoon. Stir well after each addition. Stir in flour, raisins, coconut, vanilla and salt. Spread in prepared pan. Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: brocoli delight
directions: Cut tops of broccoli into bite size pieces.
Cut bacon into bite size pieces and fry until crisp.
Drain.
Combine broccoli, bacon, onion, raisins and cashews in salad bowl.
Make dressing of mayo, sugar and vinegar.
Let dressing set until sugar dissolves. Add more broccoli if desired and serve.

title: texas cookies
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients.
Add egg.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven about 10 minutes or until slightly brown.

title: chocolate confection cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°, grease and flour jelly roll pan.
Prepare cake following package directions for basic recipe.
Pour into pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpicks inserted in center comes out clean.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Press sauerkraut between paper towels to remove excess moisture.
Combine kraut, onion, sour cream and garlic powder; stir well.
Spoon mixture into lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle corned beef evenly over kraut mixture; top with cheese.

title: baked vegetables au gratin
directions: In skillet, melt butter and saute onion and garlic salt.
In casserole, mix beans, corn, celery, green pepper and basil.
Add sauteed onion and mix well.
Mix 1 cup of cheese in mixture.
Take bread cubes and place along outer edge of casserole, leaving the middle open.
Sprinkle the rest of cheese over top of it all. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: grandma's goulash
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onions.
Add uncooked macaroni, chopped tomato, sugar and ketchup.
Simmer with lid until macaroni is tender.

title: heavenly waffles
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour in hot waffle iron. Brown to preference. Serves 6 (2 waffles each); makes 12 (4 x 4-inch) waffles.

title: hamburger patties
directions: Combine 1/4 cup soup, ground beef, bread crumbs, egg and onion. Mix; shape into patties.
Brown patties; drain off grease.
Combine soup and water.
Spoon over beef patties and let simmer, covered, over low heat for 20 minutes.

title: sauerkraut casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
In large skillet or Dutch oven.
Cook Italian Sausage and onion until sausage is brown and onion is tender.
Drain fat.
Stir in apples, sauerkraut, water, sugar and caraway seed.
Transfer to a 2-1/2 qt. baking dish.
Cover and bake for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: tom's corn fritters
directions: Combine corn, flour, sugar, eggs, salt and oil and mix in blender.
Add milk if necessary.
Fry in hot fat.
Use a teaspoon as a measure.
Keep warm on paper towels in oven until ready to serve.
Serve with pancake syrup, jelly, powdered sugar or plain.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook together potatoes, carrots, celery and onion until tender.
Save water.
Cook 4 to 8 strips of bacon and crumble. Melt margarine; add soup, milk and sour cream.
Add vegetables, bacon and as much reserved water as you like.
Salt and pepper as desired.
Simmer.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix all this together.

title: crispy cheese wafers
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Add Rice Krispies.
Roll in small balls.
Press with fork.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Yield:
4 to 5 dozen.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until just thawed.
Drain and mix with rice. Mix soup and milk; pour over rice mixture.
Stir in cheese cubes. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well with hands and shape into small balls about the size of walnuts.
Place on cookie sheet about 1-inch apart.
Will not spread when baked so can be placed close together.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Will be brown on bottom.
Do not overcook.
Can be stored at room temperature in airtight container.
Makes about 100 balls.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Boil and mash potatoes.
Mix in sugar, butter, eggs, vanilla and milk.
Put in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients for 3 minutes.
Pour into ungreased 10-inch pie plate (glass is best).
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Do not open oven at all until 45 minutes is up.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients together.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese over top before the last 15 minutes of baking.

title: strawberry dip
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Chill.
Serve with strawberries and other fresh fruit.

title: roasted chili peppers(to roast and peel green chilies)
directions: Preheat oven to 500 degrees.

title: peter paul mounds cake
directions: Heat milk and sugar.
Add marshmallows until melted.
Add coconut.
Spread on cake while it is still hot.
Cool completely.

title: orange supreme cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine dry cake mix, coconut, 1 tablespoon orange peel, evaporated milk, 1/3 cup orange juice, 3 eggs and oil in large mixer bowl.
Mix cake as directed on package. Divide batter evenly in 2 layer pans; bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool in pans on racks 10 minutes.
Remove from pans; cool completely on racks.
Refrigerate for ease in splitting.
For orange filling, beat 3 eggs until blended in saucepan.
Stir in sugar, 3/4 cup orange juice and 1 tablespoon orange peel.
Cook; stir over low heat until thick.
Cool.
Whip cream until stiff. Fold whipped cream, vanilla extract and almond extract into egg mixture.
Split each layer into 2 thin layers.
Spread filling between layers and on top of cake.
Decorate with mandarin orange segments and toasted almonds, if desired.
Refrigerate.

title: applesauce cinnamon muffins
directions: Mix these six ingredients and add to the mixed dry ingredients.
Pour into prepared muffin tins and bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: 7 minute icing
directions: Mix and heat about 7 minutes (beat) over boiling water in double boiler.
Remove from heat; beat 1 minute.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla flavoring.

title: sandy's sticky buns
directions: Butter Bundt pan.
Put frozen rolls in pan.
Sprinkle pudding mix over rolls.
Mix margarine, sugar, pecans and cinnamon; pour over rolls.
Cover with plastic wrap and leave sitting out overnight to rise.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Place all the ingredients in large bowl.
Marinate overnight in the Italian dressing.

title: punch
directions: In blender, puree raspberries.
Add all ingredients; stir until sugar dissolves.
Add sherbet and champagne.
Stir gently.

title: kim's potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until done.
Drain well.
While potatoes are still hot, pour Garlic Expressions over and toss lightly.
Add onions, parsley, dill and seasonings and lightly toss again.
Add mayonnaise and mix.
Serve immediately or refrigerate.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet on medium heat.
Drain off fat. Using fork, crumble ground beef into pea size pieces.
In large pot combine beef and remaining ingredients.
Bring to a simmer over low heat.
Cook, stirring every 15 minutes for about 2 to 3 hours.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed; drain.
Add margarine and enough milk to cover half of noodles.
Add tuna and cream of chicken soup.
Stir and mix well.
Pour half of mixture into casserole dish and cover with cheese.
Next, pour remaining mixture and top with more cheese.
Bake at 400° until brown, about 15 minutes.

title: cutlets du tofu
directions: Bake in preheated oven 25 minutes at 350°.
Slice tofu, roll in seasoned bread crumbs.
Place on greased cookie sheet, turn every 15 minutes.
Saute onion, garlic and green peppers in 2 tablespoons oil.
Pour over cutlets when done.
Serve.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Combine soy sauce, garlic, onion, peppers, celery, tomatoes and 1 cup water.
Cook about 20 minutes.
Fry hamburgers in small patties until done.
Pour off grease and then pour first mixture over hamburgers in skillet.
Make 3/4 cup water and 1 tablespoon flour or cornstarch in cup.
Shake well and pour over hamburgers; simmer about 15 minutes.
Serve with rice or fried potatoes.
If it's too thick, add a little more water and stir in.

title: cherry drops
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolk and vanilla; beat well. Add flour and drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Decorate with halved, dried maraschino cherries.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Mix well then add:
1 cup grated zucchini, 1 cup grated walnuts (optional).
Mix well.
Chill for 2 hours.	Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: malt shoppe pie
directions: Combine softened ice cream and Cool Whip until blended. Reserve 8 Whoppers for garnish.
Add remaining crushed Whoppers to ice cream mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle remaining crushed Whoppers to garnish.
Freeze.
Also good with chocolate wafers and cookie pie crust.

title: refrigerator vegetable salad
directions: Drain first 4 ingredients.
Add celery, onion and green pepper.
Bring to boil the vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper and water. Pour over vegetables.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: chicken and cheese
directions: Place chicken breasts in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Alternate pieces of cheese over the chicken. In a separate bowl mix soup, milk and water.
Pour over chicken and cheese.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Serve over rice or with potato.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until top is golden brown and sides bubbling.

title: chris' belly buttons
directions: Separate ham slices and blot moisture off with paper towel. Spread cream cheese on slice.
Place green onion on edge and roll the slice of ham around the onion.
Slice across, making belly buttons.
They're very attractive at parties and delicious, too!
